          <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">What Is Equipment Finance?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Equipment finance is a broad category of commercial lending that helps Australian businesses acquire the tools, machinery, vehicles, technology, and other physical assets they need to operate and grow — without paying the full cost upfront. Instead of tying up working capital in a large purchase, you spread the cost over the useful life of the equipment through regular repayments.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">In Australia, equipment finance is one of the most commonly used forms of business lending. The Australian Finance Industry Association (AFIA) reports that over $50 billion in new equipment and vehicle finance is written annually. From a single tradesperson buying a work ute to a construction company acquiring a fleet of excavators, equipment finance makes business growth accessible without depleting cash reserves.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The Australian government supports equipment investment through the instant asset write-off scheme (currently allowing businesses with aggregated turnover under $10 million to immediately deduct the full cost of eligible assets up to $20,000 per asset) and other depreciation provisions. Your finance structure determines how these tax benefits are claimed — which is why choosing the right structure matters as much as choosing the right lender.</p>
        </section>

