          <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Chattel Mortgage</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">You own the equipment from day one. The lender holds a mortgage (security interest) over the asset. You claim GST upfront, deduct interest and depreciation. Best for GST-registered businesses wanting maximum tax benefits. This is the most popular structure for vehicle and equipment purchases in Australia.</p>

          <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Hire Purchase</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The finance company purchases the equipment and hires it to you. You gain ownership at the end of the term after making all payments (including any residual). You can claim interest and depreciation. GST is payable on each instalment rather than upfront. Good for businesses that prefer to spread their GST liability.</p>

          <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Finance Lease</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The lender owns the equipment and leases it to you for a fixed term. You may have the option to purchase at the end for a residual value, return the equipment, or re-lease. Lease payments are generally fully tax-deductible as an operating expense. Equipment does not appear as an asset on your balance sheet (off-balance-sheet financing), which can be advantageous for certain businesses.</p>

          <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Operating Lease / Rental</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Similar to a finance lease but typically shorter term, with the equipment returned at the end. Best for technology and equipment that becomes obsolete quickly — you upgrade rather than own. All payments are fully deductible. No residual risk. Popular for IT equipment, medical technology, and fleet vehicles where staying current matters more than ownership.</p>

